      "seed": 151835866,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773953779219,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "text": "1] TurnTracker: To have the LLM ROC recursion stopped, to avoid latency\n\n2) SessionsState as context: Giving hardcodes rules to be in same format, Giving 30\nconversation history\n\n3] Testing: Was challenge had to do 3P setup. I looked at existing bultin plugin and\nassumed it as custom plugin and created a setup for team\n\n4.1] GuardRail (LLM OP sanitizer): Some REgEx, Remove Blocklisted words,\nhttps://docs.aws.amazon.com/comprehend/latest/dg/trust-safety.html.Reused\nthis but we wanted to change this in long-run \"I can't assist with that request.\"\n\n4.2] GuardRail (User IP sanitizer): Some RegEx, Remove Blocklisted words,\nhttps://docs.aws.amazon.com/comprehend/latest/dg/trust-safety.html. Reused\nthis but we wanted to change this in long-run \"I can't assist with that request.\"\n\n5] Token Usage tracking: 1 word = 0.75 token. No visibility. Had to approximate\n\n6] ActionGroupPer agent 20 Action group per agent with 10 APls in each. Trade offs.\n\n7] Language Programming Interface: Science came up with some simplification. Own\nit in Bedrock. It would make sense for their team to own it.\n\n8] IDC setup was missed before 1 week: That as a blunder.\n\n9] Bidirectional streaming over hits: The client and server can send data to each other\ncontinuously and independently over a single secure HTTP connection\n\n10] Orchestrator is a distributed LangChain which is composable stateful engine.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "HOR8tefpcjjC84YjWrbnz",
      "originalText": "1] TurnTracker: To have the LLM ROC recursion stopped, to avoid latency\n\n2) SessionsState as context: Giving hardcodes rules to be in same format, Giving 30 conversation history\n\n3] Testing: Was challenge had to do 3P setup. I looked at existing bultin plugin and assumed it as custom plugin and created a setup for team\n\n4.1] GuardRail (LLM OP sanitizer): Some REgEx, Remove Blocklisted words, https://docs.aws.amazon.com/comprehend/latest/dg/trust-safety.html.Reused\nthis but we wanted to change this in long-run \"I can't assist with that request.\"\n\n4.2] GuardRail (User IP sanitizer): Some RegEx, Remove Blocklisted words, https://docs.aws.amazon.com/comprehend/latest/dg/trust-safety.html. Reused\nthis but we wanted to change this in long-run \"I can't assist with that request.\"\n\n5] Token Usage tracking: 1 word = 0.75 token. No visibility. Had to approximate\n\n6] ActionGroupPer agent 20 Action group per agent with 10 APls in each. Trade offs.\n\n7] Language Programming Interface: Science came up with some simplification. Own it in Bedrock. It would make sense for their team to own it.\n\n8] IDC setup was missed before 1 week: That as a blunder.\n\n9] Bidirectional streaming over hits: The client and server can send data to each other continuously and independently over a single secure HTTP connection\n\n10] Orchestrator is a distributed LangChain which is composable stateful engine.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    }
  ],
